      "source": [
        "import tensorflow as tf\n",
        "from tensorflow import keras\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "# Load the MNIST dataset\n",
        "(x_train, y_train), (x_test, y_test) = keras.datasets.mnist.load_data()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Normalize the input data\n",
        "x_train = x_train.astype('float32') / 255\n",
        "x_test = x_test.astype('float32') / 255\n",
        "\n",
        "# Flatten the input images\n",
        "x_train = x_train.reshape(x_train.shape[0], -1)\n",
        "x_test = x_test.reshape(x_test.shape[0], -1)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Create the model\n",
        "model = keras.Sequential([\n",
        "    keras.layers.Dense(128, activation='relu', input_shape=(784,)),\n",
        "    keras.layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),\n",
        "    keras.layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax')\n",
        "])\n",
        "\n",
        "# Compile the model\n",
        "model.compile(optimizer='adam',\n",
        "              loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',\n",
        "              metrics=['accuracy'])\n",
        "\n",
        "# Train the model\n",
        "history = model.fit(x_train, y_train, epochs=10, batch_size=32, validation_split=0.2)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Evaluate the model\n",
        "test_loss, test_acc = model.evaluate(x_test, y_test)\n",
        "print(f\"Test accuracy: {test_acc:.4f}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Make predictions\n",
        "predictions = model.predict(x_test)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Plot some example predictions\n",
        "fig, axes = plt.subplots(3, 3, figsize=(12, 12))\n",
        "for i, ax in enumerate(axes.flat):\n",
        "    ax.imshow(x_test[i].reshape(28, 28), cmap='gray')\n",
        "    predicted_label = np.argmax(predictions[i])\n",
        "    true_label = y_test[i]\n",
        "    ax.set_title(f\"Predicted: {predicted_label}, True: {true_label}\")\n",
        "    ax.axis('off')\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Plot training history\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 4))\n",
        "plt.subplot(121)\n",
        "plt.plot(history.history['accuracy'], label='Training Accuracy')\n",
        "plt.plot(history.history['val_accuracy'], label='Validation Accuracy')\n",
        "plt.title('Model Accuracy')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Epoch')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Accuracy')\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.subplot(122)\n",
        "plt.plot(history.history['loss'], label='Training Loss')\n",
        "plt.plot(history.history['val_loss'], label='Validation Loss')\n",
        "plt.title('Model Loss')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Epoch')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Loss')\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],

      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "from sklearn.datasets import load_breast_cancer\n",
        "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
        "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
        "from sklearn.neural_network import MLPClassifier\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import classification_report, confusion_matrix\n",
        "\n",
        "# Load the Breast Cancer dataset\n",
        "cancer = load_breast_cancer()\n",
        "X, y = cancer.data, cancer.target\n",
        "\n",
        "# Split the data into training and testing sets\n",
        "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.3, random_state=42)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Standardize the features\n",
        "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
        "X_train_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_train)\n",
        "X_test_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Create and train the MLP\n",
        "mlp = MLPClassifier(hidden_layer_sizes=(30, 15), activation='relu', solver='adam',\n",
        "                    max_iter=1000, random_state=42, early_stopping=True,\n",
        "                    validation_fraction=0.1)\n",
        "mlp.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Make predictions\n",
        "y_pred = mlp.predict(X_test_scaled)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Print the classification report and confusion matrix\n",
        "print(\"Classification Report:\")\n",
        "print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred, target_names=cancer.target_names))\n",
        "print(\"\\nConfusion Matrix:\")\n",
        "print(confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred))\n",
        "\n",
        "# Plot the learning curve\n",
        "from sklearn.model_selection import learning_curve\n",
        "\n",
        "train_sizes, train_scores, test_scores = learning_curve(\n",
        "    mlp, X_train_scaled, y_train, cv=5, n_jobs=-1,\n",
        "    train_sizes=np.linspace(0.1, 1.0, 10))\n",
        "\n",
        "train_mean = np.mean(train_scores, axis=1)\n",
        "train_std = np.std(train_scores, axis=1)\n",
        "test_mean = np.mean(test_scores, axis=1)\n",
        "test_std = np.std(test_scores, axis=1)\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
        "plt.plot(train_sizes, train_mean, label='Training score', color='blue')\n",
        "plt.fill_between(train_sizes, train_mean - train_std, train_mean + train_std, alpha=0.1, color='blue')\n",
        "plt.plot(train_sizes, test_mean, label='Cross-validation score', color='red')\n",
        "plt.fill_between(train_sizes, test_mean - test_std, test_mean + test_std, alpha=0.1, color='red')\n",
        "plt.title('Learning Curve for Breast Cancer Classification')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Training Size')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Score')\n",
        "plt.legend(loc='best')\n",
        "plt.grid(True)\n",
        "plt.show()"

        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import tensorflow as tf\n",
        "from tensorflow.keras import layers, models\n",
        "from tensorflow.keras.datasets import cifar10\n",
        "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "# Load CIFAR-10 dataset\n",
        "(x_train, y_train), (x_test, y_test) = cifar10.load_data()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Extract only dog (class 5) and cat (class 3) images\n",
        "dog_cat_indices_train = np.where((y_train == 3) | (y_train == 5))[0]\n",
        "dog_cat_indices_test = np.where((y_test == 3) | (y_test == 5))[0]\n",
        "\n",
        "x_train_dog_cat = x_train[dog_cat_indices_train]\n",
        "y_train_dog_cat = y_train[dog_cat_indices_train]\n",
        "x_test_dog_cat = x_test[dog_cat_indices_test]\n",
        "y_test_dog_cat = y_test[dog_cat_indices_test]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Convert labels to binary (0 for cat, 1 for dog)\n",
        "y_train_dog_cat = (y_train_dog_cat == 5).astype(int)\n",
        "y_test_dog_cat = (y_test_dog_cat == 5).astype(int)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Normalize pixel values\n",
        "x_train_dog_cat = x_train_dog_cat.astype('float32') / 255\n",
        "x_test_dog_cat = x_test_dog_cat.astype('float32') / 255\n",
        "\n",
        "# Split the data into training and validation sets\n",
        "x_train, x_val, y_train, y_val = train_test_split(x_train_dog_cat, y_train_dog_cat, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Create the model\n",
        "model = models.Sequential([\n",
        "    layers.Conv2D(32, (3, 3), activation='relu', input_shape=(32, 32, 3)),\n",
        "    layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)),\n",
        "    layers.Conv2D(64, (3, 3), activation='relu'),\n",
        "    layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)),\n",
        "    layers.Conv2D(64, (3, 3), activation='relu'),\n",
        "    layers.Flatten(),\n",
        "    layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),\n",
        "    layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')\n",
        "])\n",
        "\n",
        "# Compile the model\n",
        "model.compile(optimizer='adam',\n",
        "              loss='binary_crossentropy',\n",
        "              metrics=['accuracy'])\n",
        "\n",
        "# Train the model\n",
        "history = model.fit(x_train, y_train, epochs=10,\n",
        "                    validation_data=(x_val, y_val))\n",
        "\n",
        "# Evaluate the model\n",
        "test_loss, test_acc = model.evaluate(x_test_dog_cat, y_test_dog_cat, verbose=2)\n",
        "print(f'\\nTest accuracy: {test_acc}')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Plot training history\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 4))\n",
        "plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)\n",
        "plt.plot(history.history['accuracy'], label='Training Accuracy')\n",
        "plt.plot(history.history['val_accuracy'], label='Validation Accuracy')\n",
        "plt.title('Model Accuracy')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Epoch')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Accuracy')\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)\n",
        "plt.plot(history.history['loss'], label='Training Loss')\n",

        "plt.xlabel('Epoch')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Loss')\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()"

        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import tensorflow as tf\n",
        "from tensorflow.keras import layers, models\n",

        "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "# Load CIFAR-10 dataset\n",
        "(x_train, y_train), (x_test, y_test) = cifar10.load_data()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Extract only truck (class 9), automobile (class 1), and airplane (class 0) images\n",
        "class_indices = [9, 1, 0]\n",
        "mask_train = np.isin(y_train, class_indices)\n",
        "mask_test = np.isin(y_test, class_indices)\n",
        "\n",
        "x_train_filtered = x_train[mask_train.reshape(-1)]\n",
        "y_train_filtered = y_train[mask_train.reshape(-1)]\n",
        "x_test_filtered = x_test[mask_test.reshape(-1)]\n",
        "y_test_filtered = y_test[mask_test.reshape(-1)]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Remap labels to 0, 1, 2\n",
        "label_map = {9: 0, 1: 1, 0: 2}\n",
        "y_train_filtered = np.vectorize(label_map.get)(y_train_filtered)\n",
        "y_test_filtered = np.vectorize(label_map.get)(y_test_filtered)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Convert to categorical\n",
        "y_train_cat = tf.keras.utils.to_categorical(y_train_filtered, 3)\n",
        "y_test_cat = tf.keras.utils.to_categorical(y_test_filtered, 3)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Normalize pixel values\n",

        "\n",
        "# Split the data into training and validation sets\n",

        "\n",
        "# Create the model\n",
        "model = models.Sequential([\n",
        "    layers.Conv2D(32, (3, 3), activation='relu', input_shape=(32, 32, 3)),\n",
        "    layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)),\n",
        "    layers.Conv2D(64, (3, 3), activation='relu'),\n",
        "    layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)),\n",
        "    layers.Conv2D(64, (3, 3), activation='relu'),\n",
        "    layers.Flatten(),\n",
        "    layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),\n",
        "    layers.Dense(3, activation='softmax')\n",
        "])\n",

        "# Compile the model\n",
        "model.compile(optimizer='adam',\n",
        "              loss='categorical_crossentropy',\n",

        "\n",
        "# Call the function to predict and display images from the test set\n",
        "predict_and_display(model, x_test_filtered, y_test_cat, class_names)\n"

      "source": [
        "import tensorflow as tf\n",
        "from tensorflow.keras import layers, models, optimizers\n",
        "from tensorflow.keras.datasets import mnist\n",
        "from tensorflow.keras.utils import to_categorical\n",
        "(x_train, y_train), (x_test, y_test) = mnist.load_data()\n",
        "x_train = x_train.astype('float32') / 255.0\n",
        "x_test = x_test.astype('float32') / 255.0\n",
        "y_train = to_categorical(y_train, 10)\n",
        "y_test = to_categorical(y_test, 10)\n",
        "base_model = tf.keras.applications.MobileNetV2(input_shape=(224, 224, 3),\n",
        "                                               include_top=False,\n",
        "                                               weights='imagenet')\n",
        "model = models.Sequential()\n",
        "model.add(layers.Reshape((28, 28, 1), input_shape=(28, 28)))  # Add a channel dimension\n",
        "model.add(layers.Conv2D(32, (3, 3), activation='relu'))\n",
        "model.add(layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)))\n",
        "model.add(layers.Flatten())\n",
        "model.add(layers.Dense(256, activation='relu'))\n",
        "model.add(layers.Dropout(0.5))\n",
        "model.add(layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax'))\n",
        "for layer in base_model.layers:\n",
        "    layer.trainable = False\n",
        "model.compile(optimizer=optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.001),\n",
        "              loss='categorical_crossentropy',\n",
        "              metrics=['accuracy'])"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "9e5iuYpew_o8"
      },
      "execution_count": 11,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "epochs = 1\n",
        "batch_size = 32\n",
        "\n",
        "# Create tf.data.Dataset for training and validation\n",
        "train_dataset = tf.data.Dataset.from_tensor_slices((x_train, y_train)).shuffle(60000).batch(batch_size)\n",
        "val_dataset = tf.data.Dataset.from_tensor_slices((x_test, y_test)).batch(batch_size)\n",
        "\n",
        "for epoch in range(epochs):\n",
        "    print(f\"Epoch {epoch + 1}/{epochs}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Training loop\n",
        "    for images, labels in train_dataset:\n",
        "        with tf.GradientTape() as tape:\n",
        "            predictions = model(images)\n",
        "            loss = tf.keras.losses.categorical_crossentropy(labels, predictions)\n",
        "        gradients = tape.gradient(loss, model.trainable_variables)\n",
        "        optimizer = optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.001)\n",
        "        optimizer.apply_gradients(zip(gradients, model.trainable_variables))\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Validation loop\n",
        "    accuracy = tf.metrics.CategoricalAccuracy()\n",
        "    for images, labels in val_dataset:\n",
